events.event_name: Trump's announcement on China's soybean purchases
events.description: US President Donald Trump stated that China plans to increase its purchases of US soybeans to 20 million tons this season and 25 million tons next season.

events.event_name: US Treasury guidance on biofuel tax credits
events.description: The US Treasury provided updated guidance on biofuel tax credits, offering clarity for producers.
Upcoming crop forecasts from the USDA expected to provide market direction.

facts.fact_text: Soybean futures rose nearly 3% to $10.95 per bushel on Wednesday.

evidences.evidence_text: Soybean futures rose nearly 3% to $10.95 per bushel on Wednesday, the highest in two months

facts.fact_text: China plans to lift purchases of US soybeans to 20 million tons this season and 25 million tons next season.

evidences.evidence_text: US President Donald Trump said China plans to lift purchases of US soybeans to 20 million tons this season and 25 million tons next season.

facts.fact_text: China had bought about 12 million tons of US soybeans by late January.

evidences.evidence_text: By late January, China had already bought about 12 million tons, meeting a US pledge following the late-October trade truce.

claims.claim_text: China’s purchases are closely watched for signs of further demand.

evidences.evidence_text: As the world’s largest buyer of US soybeans, China’s purchases are closely watched for signs of further demand

claims.claim_text: Ample global supply continues to limit price gains for soybeans.

evidences.evidence_text: Despite these bullish factors, ample global supply continues to limit price gains

evidence.evidence_text: Soybean futures rose nearly 3% to $10.95 per bushel on Wednesday... after US President Donald Trump said China plans to lift purchases
Traders also welcomed updated US Treasury guidance on biofuel tax credits, providing clarity for biofuel producers.
